sql_command: SELECT c.cus_name, SUM(a.acc_bal) AS total_balance FROM customers c JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id GROUP BY c.id, c.cus_name ORDER BY total_balance DESC LIMIT 5;

query: Calculate the percentage of blocked cards per branch.
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WITH b, COUNT(card) AS blockedCards
MATCH (b)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c2:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card2:Cards)
WITH b, blockedCards, COUNT(card2) AS totalCards
RETURN b.branch_id, (blockedCards * 100.0 / totalCards) AS percentageBlockedCards

query: What was the total transaction amount last month for all customers in the 'CHI-03' branch?

FROM transactions
JOIN accounts ON transactions.acc_id = accounts.id
JOIN customers ON accounts.cus_id = customers.id
JOIN branches ON customers.brc = branches.id
WHERE branches.brc = 'CHI-03'
AND transactions.tran_dt >= date_trunc('month', NOW()) - INTERVAL '1 month'

WHERE c.branch_id = 'CHI-03' AND date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year, month: date().month - 1, day: 1 })

RETURN SUM(t.transaction_amount) AS total_transaction_amount

WHERE dt.de_type = 'Retirement';
cypher_command:
MATCH (d:Deposits)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(c:Customers)-[:HAS_DEPOSIT_TYPE]->(dt:DepositTypes)
WHERE dt.type = 'Retirement'
RETURN SUM(d.balance) AS total_retirement_deposit_balance

query: How many customers have an average transaction amount of more than $500?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) FROM customers c JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id JOIN transactions t ON a.id = t.acc_id GROUP BY c.id HAVING AVG(t.tran_amt) > 500;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH c, AVG(t.transaction_amount) AS avg_transaction_amount
WHERE avg_transaction_amount > 500
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: How many loans are set to be fully paid off by the end of the current calendar year?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM loans WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM ln_en_dt) = EXTRACT(YEAR FROM CURRENT_DATE);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WHERE date(l.end_date) <= date({ year: date().year, month: 12, day: 31 })
RETURN count(l) AS loans_to_be_paid_off

query: How many customers have a phone number with the '310' area code?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE cus_phone LIKE '%310%';
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)
WHERE c.phone STARTS WITH '310'
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: What was the total value of all transactions made during the last calendar week?
sql_command: SELECT SUM(tran_amt) AS total_value FROM transactions WHERE tran_dt >= DATE_TRUNC('week', CURRENT_DATE) - INTERVAL '1 week' AND tran_dt < DATE_TRUNC('week', CURRENT_DATE);
cypher_command:
MATCH (t:Transactions)
WHERE date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year, month: date().month, day: date().day - 7 }) 
RETURN sum(t.transaction_amount) AS total_transaction_value

query: How many customers have a deposit with an interest rate lower than the bank's lowest loan rate?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT deposits.cus_id) FROM deposits WHERE deposits.interest < (SELECT MIN(loans.interest) FROM loans);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WHERE d.interest_rate < l.interest_rate
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many unique customers performed a transaction in the last 24 hours?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE t.transaction_date >= datetime().epochMillis - 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c.customer_id) AS unique_customers

query: How many customers share a birthday with at least one other customer?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c1.id) AS customer_count FROM customers c1 JOIN customers c2 ON c1.cus_dob = c2.cus_dob AND c1.id <> c2.id;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c1:Customers), (c2:Customers)
WHERE c1.customer_id <> c2.customer_id AND c1.date_of_birth = c2.date_of_birth
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c1.customer_id) AS shared_birthday_customers

query: How many unblocked cards have a balance greater than $10,000?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cards WHERE is_blocked = FALSE AND bal > 10000;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE card.is_blocked = false AND card.balance > 10000
RETURN count(card) AS unblocked_cards_with_high_balance

query: Find the number of customers who have an account but do not possess any cards.
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customers.id) FROM customers 
JOIN accounts ON customers.id = accounts.cus_id 
LEFT JOIN cards ON customers.id = cards.cus_id 
WHERE cards.id IS NULL;

query: What is the total account balance for accounts with more than 20 transactions this month?
sql_command:
SELECT SUM(a.acc_bal) as total_balance
FROM accounts a
JOIN transactions t ON a.id = t.acc_id
WHERE t.tran_dt >= DATE_TRUNC('month', CURRENT_DATE) 
GROUP BY a.id
HAVING COUNT(t.id) > 20;
cypher_command:
MATCH (a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year, month: date().month, day: 1 })
WITH a, count(t) AS transaction_count
WHERE transaction_count > 20
RETURN sum(a.account_balance) AS total_account_balance

query: How many customers opened their first account with the bank over 5 years ago?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) AS customer_count FROM accounts WHERE created_at < NOW() - INTERVAL '5 years';
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WHERE date(a.created_at) < date({ year: date().year - 5, month: 1, day: 1 })
RETURN count(DISTINCT c) AS customers_count

query: How many 'Auto Loan' types were granted in the year 2024?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM loans WHERE ln_type_id = (SELECT id FROM loan_types WHERE ln_type = 'Auto Loan') AND EXTRACT(YEAR FROM ln_st_dt) = 2024;
cypher_command:
MATCH (l:Loans)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(c:Customers)
WHERE l.start_date >= date({ year: 2024, month: 1, day: 1 }) AND l.start_date < date({ year: 2025, month: 1, day: 1 })
AND (l)-[:HAS_LOAN_TYPE]->(:LoanTypes {type: 'Auto Loan'})
RETURN count(l) AS auto_loan_count

query: What is the count of customers with the last name 'Jones'?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE cus_name LIKE '% Jones'
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)
WHERE c.customer_name = 'Jones'
RETURN count(c) AS customer_count

query: How many accounts have a balance higher than the average account balance of their branch?
cypher_command:
MATCH (a:Accounts)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(c:Customers)
WITH c.branch_id AS branchId, AVG(a.account_balance) AS avgBalance
MATCH (a:Accounts)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(c:Customers)
WHERE a.account_balance > avgBalance AND c.branch_id = branchId
RETURN COUNT(a) AS accountsAboveAverage

query: Count how many customers have all of their associated cards active (not blocked).
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) FROM cards WHERE is_blocked = False AND cus_id NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT cus_id FROM cards WHERE is_blocked = True AND cus_id IS NOT NULL);
cypher_command: MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards) WHERE card.is_blocked = false WITH c, COUNT(card) AS activeCardCount MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(allCards:Cards) WITH c, activeCardCount, COUNT(allCards) AS totalCardCount WHERE activeCardCount = totalCardCount RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customerCount

query: How many deposits are scheduled to mature in the next calendar quarter?
cypher_command:
MATCH (d:Deposits)
WHERE date(d.end_date) >= date({ year: date().year, month: date().month + 1, day: 1 }) 
  AND date(d.end_date) < date({ year: date().year, month: date().month + 3, day: 1 })
RETURN count(d) AS scheduled_deposits

query: What is the total number of transactions made by customers who currently have a 'Home Equity' loan?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM transactions t
JOIN loans l ON l.cus_id = t.acc_id
JOIN loan_types lt ON l.ln_type_id = lt.id
WHERE lt.ln_type = 'Home Equity';
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans {loan_type_id: 'Home Equity'})<-[:HAS_LOAN_TYPE]-(lType:LoanTypes)
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
RETURN COUNT(t) AS total_transactions

query: How many customers have a total outstanding loan balance of more than $500,000?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) FROM loans WHERE bal < -500000;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH c, SUM(l.balance) AS total_loan_balance
WHERE total_loan_balance > 500000
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: What is the total number of transactions that occurred on a weekend (Saturday or Sunday)?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) AS weekend_transaction_count FROM transactions WHERE EXTRACT(DOW FROM tran_dt) IN (0, 6)
cypher_command:
MATCH (t:Transactions)
WHERE date(t.transaction_date).dayOfWeek IN [6, 7]
RETURN COUNT(t) AS total_weekend_transactions

query: How many customers are registered with the branch located at '123 Finance St'?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(customers.id) 
FROM customers 
JOIN branches ON customers.brc = branches.id 
WHERE branches.brc_address = '123 Finance St'
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]->(b:Branches {branch_address: '123 Finance St'})
RETURN count(c) AS registered_customers

query: How many loan types have an average interest rate below 3.5%?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT lt.id) AS low_interest_loan_type_count
FROM loan_types lt
JOIN loans l ON lt.id = l.ln_type_id
GROUP BY lt.id
HAVING AVG(l.interest) < 3.5;
cypher_command:
MATCH (lt:LoanTypes)<-[:HAS_LOAN_TYPE]-(l:Loans)
WITH lt, AVG(l.interest_rate) AS avg_interest_rate
WHERE avg_interest_rate < 3.5
RETURN COUNT(lt) AS loan_type_count

query: Count the number of customers who have deposits with the bank but have no loans.
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT d.cus_id) 
FROM deposits d
LEFT JOIN loans l ON d.cus_id = l.cus_id
WHERE l.cus_id IS NULL;

query: What is the total account balance for customers under the age of 30?
sql_command: SELECT SUM(acc_bal) AS total_balance FROM accounts JOIN customers ON accounts.cus_id = customers.id WHERE AGE(customers.cus_dob) < INTERVAL '30 years'
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WHERE date().year - date(c.date_of_birth).year < 30
RETURN SUM(a.account_balance) AS total_account_balance

query: How many branches have an average customer account balance greater than $25,000?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT branches.id) 
FROM branches 
JOIN accounts ON branches.id = accounts.id 
GROUP BY branches.id 
HAVING AVG(accounts.acc_bal) > 25000;
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WITH b, AVG(a.account_balance) AS avg_balance
WHERE avg_balance > 25000
RETURN COUNT(b) AS branch_count

query: Count the number of active (not blocked) cards that expire in or after the year 2030.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cards WHERE is_blocked = FALSE AND EXTRACT(YEAR FROM card_exp_date) >= 2030;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE card.is_blocked = false AND date(card.expiration_date) >= date('2030-01-01')
RETURN count(card) AS active_cards_count

query: What is the total transaction amount from accounts that were opened in the last 6 months?
sql_command:
SELECT SUM(t.tran_amt) AS total_transaction_amount 
FROM transactions t
JOIN accounts a ON t.acc_id = a.id
WHERE a.created_at >= NOW() - INTERVAL '6 months';

query: How many customers have a '@yahoo.com' email address?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers WHERE cus_email LIKE '%@yahoo.com'
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)
WHERE c.email ENDS WITH '@yahoo.com'
RETURN COUNT(c) AS yahoo_customers_count

query: How many customers have a total loan balance that is higher than their combined total balance from accounts and deposits?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS num_customers
FROM customers c
JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id
JOIN (
    SELECT cus_id, SUM(acc_bal) AS total_account_balance
    FROM accounts
    GROUP BY cus_id
) a ON c.id = a.cus_id
JOIN (
    SELECT cus_id, SUM(bal) AS total_deposit_balance
    FROM deposits
    GROUP BY cus_id
) d ON c.id = d.cus_id
WHERE ABS(l.bal) > (a.total_account_balance + d.total_deposit_balance);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WITH c, SUM(l.balance) AS total_loan_balance, 
     SUM(a.account_balance) + SUM(d.balance) AS total_account_deposit_balance
WHERE total_loan_balance > total_account_deposit_balance
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers took out their first loan within 60 days of opening their first account?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS customer_count
FROM customers c
JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id
JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id
GROUP BY c.id
HAVING MIN(a.created_at) <= MIN(l.ln_st_dt) AND MIN(l.ln_st_dt) <= MIN(a.created_at) + INTERVAL '60 days';
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WHERE date(l.created_at) <= date(a.created_at) + duration('P60D')
RETURN count(DISTINCT c) AS first_time_loan_customers

query: Count the number of customers who hold active loans from three or more different loan categories.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) FROM (SELECT cus_id, COUNT(DISTINCT ln_type_id) AS loan_type_count FROM loans WHERE ln_en_dt IS NULL GROUP BY cus_id HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ln_type_id) >= 3) AS customer_with_multiple_loan_types;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH c, COUNT(DISTINCT l.loan_type_id) AS loanCategoryCount
WHERE loanCategoryCount >= 3
RETURN COUNT(c) AS activeCustomersWithMultipleLoanCategories

query: How many customers have made a single transaction that was larger than their current total account balance?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) FROM ( SELECT a.cus_id FROM transactions t JOIN accounts a ON t.acc_id = a.id WHERE t.tran_amt > a.acc_bal GROUP BY a.cus_id HAVING COUNT(t.id) = 1 ) AS customers_with_single_large_transaction;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE t.transaction_amount > a.account_balance
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS single_transaction_customers

query: How many customers made at least one transaction in every month of the previous calendar year?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year - 1, month: 1, day: 1 }) 
  AND date(t.transaction_date) < date({ year: date().year, month: 1, day: 1 })
WITH c, COUNT(DISTINCT date(t.transaction_date)) AS months
WHERE months = 12
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have a loan with an interest rate higher than the average deposit interest rate at their branch?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WITH c, AVG(d.interest_rate) AS avg_deposit_interest_rate, l.interest_rate AS loan_interest_rate
WHERE loan_interest_rate > avg_deposit_interest_rate
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: Find the number of customers who opened an account, took a loan, and got a card all within the same calendar year.
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT a.cus_id) AS num_customers
FROM accounts a
JOIN loans l ON a.cus_id = l.cus_id
JOIN cards c ON a.cus_id = c.cus_id
WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM a.created_at) = EXTRACT(YEAR FROM l.created_at)
AND EXTRACT(YEAR FROM a.created_at) = EXTRACT(YEAR FROM c.created_at);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts),
      (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans),
      (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE date(a.created_at) >= date({ year: date().year, month: 1, day: 1 }) AND 
      date(l.created_at) >= date({ year: date().year, month: 1, day: 1 }) AND 
      date(card.created_at) >= date({ year: date().year, month: 1, day: 1 })
RETURN count(DISTINCT c) AS numberOfCustomers

query: Count customers whose transaction count increased by 100% from the month before last to last month.
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH c, 
     COUNT(CASE WHEN date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year, month: date().month - 1, day: 1 }) THEN 1 END) AS last_month_count,
     COUNT(CASE WHEN date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year, month: date().month - 2, day: 1 }) AND date(t.transaction_date) < date({ year: date().year, month: date().month - 1, day: 1 }) THEN 1 END) AS month_before_last_count
WHERE last_month_count >= 2 * month_before_last_count
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have a 'Mortgage' where their total account balance is less than a single monthly payment (balance/payment_term)?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WHERE l.loan_type_id = 'Mortgage' AND c.account_balance < (l.balance / toInteger(l.payment_term))
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: Find the number of customers who have made transactions on more than 5 consecutive days.
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions) 
WITH c, date(t.transaction_date) AS trans_date 
ORDER BY trans_date 
WITH c, trans_date, COLLECT(trans_date) AS dates 
WHERE SIZE(dates) > 5 AND ALL(i IN RANGE(0, SIZE(dates)-2) WHERE date(dates[i]) + duration('P1D') = date(dates[i+1])) 
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers' total deposit term (sum of months) is greater than their total loan payment term (sum of months)?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT d.cus_id) 
FROM (SELECT cus_id, SUM(CAST(SUBSTRING(tem FROM 1 FOR LENGTH(tem)-1) AS INTEGER)) AS total_deposit_term 
      FROM deposits 
      GROUP BY cus_id) d 
JOIN (SELECT cus_id, SUM(CAST(SUBSTRING(pmt_term FROM 1 FOR LENGTH(pmt_term)-1) AS INTEGER)) AS total_loan_term 
      FROM loans 
      GROUP BY cus_id) l 
ON d.cus_id = l.cus_id 
WHERE d.total_deposit_term > l.total_loan_term;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH c, SUM(toInteger(d.term)) AS totalDepositTerm, SUM(toInteger(l.payment_term)) AS totalLoanPaymentTerm
WHERE totalDepositTerm > totalLoanPaymentTerm
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customersCount

query: Count customers whose second loan was of a different type than their first ever loan.
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l1:Loans), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l2:Loans)
WHERE l1.loan_id <> l2.loan_id AND l1.loan_type_id <> l2.loan_type_id
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have a total transaction value that's over 20 times the balance of their oldest account?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customers.id)
FROM customers
JOIN accounts ON customers.id = accounts.cus_id
JOIN transactions ON accounts.id = transactions.acc_id
WHERE (SELECT SUM(tran_amt) FROM transactions WHERE acc_id = accounts.id) > 20 * accounts.acc_bal
AND accounts.created_at = (
    SELECT MIN(created_at) FROM accounts WHERE cus_id = customers.id
);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
MATCH (a)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH c, a, SUM(t.transaction_amount) AS total_transaction_value, MIN(a.created_at) AS oldest_account_date
WHERE total_transaction_value > 20 * a.account_balance AND date(a.created_at) = date(oldest_account_date)
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: Count 'dormant whales': customers with over $1M in total balance (accounts+deposits) but no transactions in 6 months.
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS dormant_whales_count
FROM customers c
JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id
JOIN deposits d ON c.id = d.cus_id
LEFT JOIN transactions t ON a.id = t.acc_id AND t.tran_dt >= NOW() - INTERVAL '6 months'
WHERE a.acc_bal + d.bal > 1000000 AND t.id IS NULL;

query: How many customers have only one type of product with the bank (e.g., only accounts, or only loans, but not both)?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers c 
LEFT JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id 
LEFT JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id 
WHERE (a.id IS NULL OR l.id IS NULL) AND NOT (a.id IS NULL AND l.id IS NULL);

query: How many customers have a card balance that is greater than the average account balance of all customers in their branch?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cards.cus_id) FROM cards JOIN customers ON cards.cus_id = customers.id JOIN accounts ON customers.id = accounts.cus_id WHERE cards.bal < (SELECT AVG(acc_bal) FROM accounts WHERE accounts.cus_id = customers.id)
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
MATCH (b:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c)
WITH c, AVG(a.account_balance) AS avg_balance
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE card.balance > avg_balance
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: Count customers with a trend of at least 4 consecutively increasing transaction amounts.
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH c, t
ORDER BY t.transaction_date
WITH c, collect(t.transaction_amount) AS amounts
WHERE size(amounts) >= 4 AND all(i IN range(0, size(amounts)-2) WHERE amounts[i] < amounts[i+1])
RETURN count(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have a loan that started on the same day of the week they were born?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers c JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id WHERE EXTRACT(DOW FROM c.cus_dob) = EXTRACT(DOW FROM l.ln_st_dt);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WHERE date(l.start_date).dayOfWeek = date(c.date_of_birth).dayOfWeek
RETURN count(c) AS customer_count

query: Count customers where the time gap between their 2nd and 3rd loan was shorter than between their 1st and 2nd.
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l1:Loans), 
      (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l2:Loans), 
      (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l3:Loans)
WHERE l1.loan_id < l2.loan_id AND l2.loan_id < l3.loan_id 
  AND duration.between(date(l2.created_at), date(l3.created_at)).months < duration.between(date(l1.created_at), date(l2.created_at)).months
RETURN count(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have a greater total balance in 'Savings' deposits than in 'Auto' loans?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT d.cus_id) 
FROM deposits d
JOIN loans l ON d.cus_id = l.cus_id
JOIN deposit_types dt ON d.de_type_id = dt.id
JOIN loan_types lt ON l.ln_type_id = lt.id
WHERE dt.de_type = 'Savings' AND lt.ln_type = 'Auto Loan' AND d.bal > -l.bal;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH c, SUM(d.balance) AS total_savings, SUM(l.balance) AS total_auto_loans
WHERE total_savings > total_auto_loans
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: Count the number of branches where the total loan balance is more than three times the total deposit balance.
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
MATCH (b)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c2:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WITH b, SUM(l.balance) AS total_loan_balance, SUM(d.balance) AS total_deposit_balance
WHERE total_loan_balance > 3 * total_deposit_balance
RETURN COUNT(b) AS branch_count

query: How many customers' most frequent transaction day of the week is Friday?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE date(t.transaction_date).dayOfWeek = 5
WITH c, count(t) AS transaction_count
WITH c, transaction_count, 
     max(transaction_count) AS max_count
WHERE transaction_count = max_count
RETURN count(DISTINCT c) AS customers_with_friday_transactions

query: Count customers who have a deposit whose term in months is greater than their age in months when the deposit started.
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customers.id) AS customer_count
FROM customers
JOIN deposits ON customers.id = deposits.cus_id
WHERE 
  (CAST(SUBSTR(deposits.tem, 1, LENGTH(deposits.tem) - 1) AS INTEGER) > 0) AND 
  ((EXTRACT(YEAR FROM deposits.de_st_dt) * 12 + EXTRACT(MONTH FROM deposits.de_st_dt) - 
    (EXTRACT(YEAR FROM customers.cus_dob) * 12 + EXTRACT(MONTH FROM customers.cus_dob))) < 
  CAST(SUBSTR(deposits.tem, 1, LENGTH(deposits.tem) - 1) AS INTEGER));
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WHERE toInteger(d.term) > (date().year * 12 + date().month) - (date(c.date_of_birth).year * 12 + date(c.date_of_birth).month)
RETURN count(distinct c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers hold every single type of deposit the bank offers?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) 
FROM deposits 
WHERE cus_id IN (
    SELECT cus_id
    FROM deposits
    GROUP BY cus_id
    HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT de_type_id) = (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM deposit_types)
);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WITH c, COUNT(d) AS depositCount
MATCH (d:Deposits)
WITH c, depositCount, COUNT(d) AS totalDeposits
WHERE depositCount = totalDeposits
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customerCount

query: Count customers whose most recent transaction was for a lower amount than their overall average transaction amount.
sql_command:
WITH recent_avg_transactions AS (
    SELECT 
        acc_id,
        FIRST_VALUE(tran_amt) OVER (PARTITION BY acc_id ORDER BY tran_dt DESC) as recent_tran_amt,
        AVG(tran_amt) OVER (PARTITION BY acc_id) as avg_tran_amt
    FROM transactions
) 
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) as customer_count
FROM recent_avg_transactions rat
JOIN accounts a ON rat.acc_id = a.id
JOIN customers c ON a.cus_id = c.id
WHERE rat.recent_tran_amt < rat.avg_tran_amt;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions) 
WITH c, AVG(t.transaction_amount) AS avg_amount 
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a2:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t2:Transactions) 
WITH c, avg_amount, t2, MAX(t2.transaction_date) AS max_date 
WHERE t2.transaction_date = max_date 
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many unique addresses are shared by two or more customers?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_addr) AS unique_shared_addresses 
FROM customers
GROUP BY cus_addr
HAVING COUNT(cus_addr) > 1;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)
WITH c.address AS address, COUNT(DISTINCT c.customer_id) AS customer_count
WHERE customer_count >= 2
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT address) AS unique_address_count

query: Count customers who make more transactions on weekends (Sat, Sun) than on weekdays (Mon-Fri).
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH c, 
     COUNT(CASE WHEN date(t.transaction_date).dayOfWeek IN [6, 7] THEN 1 END) AS weekend_count,
     COUNT(CASE WHEN date(t.transaction_date).dayOfWeek IN [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] THEN 1 END) AS weekday_count
WHERE weekend_count > weekday_count
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have a card expiring in the same month and year as their oldest loan's end date?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS customer_count
FROM customers c
JOIN cards ca ON c.id = ca.cus_id
JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id
WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM ca.card_exp_date) = EXTRACT(YEAR FROM l.ln_en_dt)
  AND EXTRACT(MONTH FROM ca.card_exp_date) = EXTRACT(MONTH FROM l.ln_en_dt)
  AND l.ln_en_dt = (SELECT MIN(l2.ln_en_dt) FROM loans l2 WHERE l2.cus_id = c.id);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WITH c, l, card
WHERE date(card.expiration_date) = date(l.end_date)
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have a loan-to-assets ratio (total loans / total accounts+deposits) greater than 0.9?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) FROM customers c LEFT JOIN deposits d ON c.id = d.cus_id LEFT JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id GROUP BY c.id HAVING SUM(l.bal) / (SUM(d.bal) + SUM(l.bal)) > 0.9;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WITH c, SUM(l.balance) AS total_loans, COUNT(a) + COUNT(d) AS total_accounts_deposits
WHERE total_accounts_deposits > 0 AND (total_loans / total_accounts_deposits) > 0.9
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: Count customers who have never made a transaction larger than the bank's overall average transaction amount.
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) 
FROM customers c
LEFT JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id
LEFT JOIN (
    SELECT acc_id, MAX(tran_amt) as max_tran_amt
    FROM transactions
    GROUP BY acc_id
) t ON a.id = t.acc_id
WHERE t.max_tran_amt IS NULL OR t.max_tran_amt < (
    SELECT AVG(tran_amt)
    FROM transactions
);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions) 
WITH c, AVG(t.transaction_amount) AS avgTransactionAmount, MAX(t.transaction_amount) AS maxTransactionAmount 
WHERE maxTransactionAmount <= avgTransactionAmount 
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customerCount

query: How many customers have active deposits but all of their checking/savings accounts are overdrawn?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT d.cus_id) 
FROM deposits d
JOIN accounts a ON d.cus_id = a.cus_id
GROUP BY d.cus_id
HAVING SUM(d.bal) > 0 AND SUM(CASE WHEN a.acc_bal <= 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) = COUNT(a.id);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WHERE d.balance > 0 AND a.account_balance < 0
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS active_customers_with_overdrawn_accounts

query: How many customers have at least one loan for every account they hold?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH c, COUNT(DISTINCT a) AS accountCount, COUNT(DISTINCT l) AS loanCount
WHERE accountCount = loanCount
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customerCount

query: Count loyal customers: those with the bank over 10 years who have at least 3 product types (account, loan, card, deposit).
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WHERE date(a.created_at) <= date().year - 10
WITH c, COUNT(DISTINCT a) AS accountCount
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH c, accountCount, COUNT(DISTINCT l) AS loanCount
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WITH c, accountCount, loanCount, COUNT(DISTINCT d) AS depositCount
WHERE accountCount + loanCount + depositCount >= 3
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS loyalCustomers

query: How many customers have a higher total balance in blocked cards than in their active, unblocked cards?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.cus_id) as customer_count
FROM (
  SELECT cus_id,
    SUM(CASE WHEN is_blocked THEN bal ELSE 0 END) AS blocked_balance,
    SUM(CASE WHEN NOT is_blocked THEN bal ELSE 0 END) AS active_balance
  FROM cards
  GROUP BY cus_id
) c
WHERE c.blocked_balance > c.active_balance;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(activeCard:Cards)
WHERE card.is_blocked = true AND activeCard.is_blocked = false
WITH c, SUM(CASE WHEN card.is_blocked THEN card.balance ELSE 0 END) AS blockedBalance, 
     SUM(CASE WHEN NOT activeCard.is_blocked THEN activeCard.balance ELSE 0 END) AS activeBalance
WHERE blockedBalance > activeBalance
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customerCount

query: Count the number of customers whose full name is a substring of another customer's full name.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c1.id) AS substring_count FROM customers c1, customers c2 WHERE c1.id <> c2.id AND c1.cus_name LIKE '%' || c2.cus_name || '%';
cypher_command:
MATCH (c1:Customers), (c2:Customers)
WHERE c1.customer_name CONTAINS c2.customer_name AND c1.customer_id <> c2.customer_id
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c1) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have a birthday this month and also made more than 10 transactions this month?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE date(c.date_of_birth) >= date({ year: date().year, month: date().month, day: 1 }) 
  AND date(c.date_of_birth) < date({ year: date().year, month: date().month + 1, day: 1 })
WITH c, count(t) AS transaction_count
WHERE transaction_count > 10
RETURN count(c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers are suspected duplicates, having the same name and date of birth as another customer?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (SELECT cus_name, cus_dob FROM customers GROUP BY cus_name, cus_dob HAVING COUNT(*) > 1) AS duplicate_customers;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c1:Customers), (c2:Customers)
WHERE c1.customer_id <> c2.customer_id AND c1.customer_name = c2.customer_name AND c1.date_of_birth = c2.date_of_birth
RETURN COUNT(*) AS suspected_duplicates

query: How many customers more than doubled their total account balance over the last year from net transactions?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) 
FROM (
    SELECT a.cus_id, SUM(t.tran_amt) AS net_transactions, a.acc_bal
    FROM accounts a
    JOIN transactions t ON a.id = t.acc_id
    WHERE t.tran_dt >= (current_date - interval '1 year')
    GROUP BY a.cus_id, a.acc_bal
    HAVING SUM(t.tran_amt) >= a.acc_bal
) AS doubled_accounts;
cypher_command: MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:TRANSACTED]-(t:Transactions) WHERE date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year - 1, month: 1, day: 1 }) WITH c, a, sum(t.transaction_amount) AS net_transactions WHERE a.account_balance > 2 * (a.account_balance - net_transactions) RETURN count(c) AS customers_more_than_doubled

query: How many customers have at least one loan that will end after all of their cards have expired?
sql_command:
SELECT DISTINCT customers.id, customers.cus_name
FROM customers
JOIN loans ON customers.id = loans.cus_id
WHERE loans.ln_en_dt > COALESCE((SELECT MAX(card_exp_date)
                                FROM cards
                                WHERE cards.cus_id = customers.id),
                               '1900-01-01')
LIMIT 5;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE l.end_date > card.expiration_date
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: Count customers who made transactions from all of their accounts on the exact same day at least once.
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) FROM (
    SELECT a.cus_id, tran_dt
    FROM transactions t
    JOIN accounts a ON t.acc_id = a.id
    GROUP BY a.cus_id, tran_dt
    HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT a.id) = (
        SELECT COUNT(*)
        FROM accounts a2
        WHERE a2.cus_id = a.cus_id
    )
) AS subquery;

query: How many customers have a loan with an interest rate in the top 1% for that specific loan type?
sql_command:
WITH TopLoans AS (
    SELECT ln_type_id, 
           PERCENTILE_CONT(0.99) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY interest) AS top_1_percent_interest
    FROM loans
    GROUP BY ln_type_id
)

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT loans.cus_id) AS customer_count
FROM loans
JOIN TopLoans ON loans.ln_type_id = TopLoans.ln_type_id
WHERE loans.interest >= TopLoans.top_1_percent_interest;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH l, c, percentileCont(l.interest_rate, 0.99) AS top1PercentInterestRate
WHERE l.interest_rate >= top1PercentInterestRate
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customerCount

query: How many branches have their oldest customer as also their wealthiest customer by total account balance?
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)
WITH b, c
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WITH b, c, a
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Accounts)
WITH b, c, a, d, min(c.date_of_birth) AS min_dob
WHERE a.account_balance = d.account_balance AND c.date_of_birth = min_dob
RETURN count(distinct b) AS branch_count

query: How many customers started a new deposit in the same month and year as their most recent loan began?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT d.cus_id) AS customer_count
FROM deposits d
JOIN loans l ON d.cus_id = l.cus_id
WHERE EXTRACT(MONTH FROM d.de_st_dt) = EXTRACT(MONTH FROM l.ln_st_dt)
  AND EXTRACT(YEAR FROM d.de_st_dt) = EXTRACT(YEAR FROM l.ln_st_dt)
  AND l.ln_st_dt = (
    SELECT MAX(l2.ln_st_dt)
    FROM loans l2
    WHERE l2.cus_id = l.cus_id
  );
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WHERE date(d.created_at) = date(l.start_date)
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have an account balance standard deviation that is greater than their average account balance?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) AS num_customers
FROM accounts
GROUP BY cus_id
HAVING STDDEV(acc_bal) > AVG(acc_bal);

query: Count customers who have taken a new loan before their previous loan's official end date.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT l1.cus_id) FROM loans l1 JOIN loans l2 ON l1.cus_id = l2.cus_id AND l1.ln_st_dt < l2.ln_st_dt AND l1.ln_en_dt > l2.ln_st_dt;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(n:Loans)
WHERE date(n.start_date) < date(l.end_date)
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers maintained a total monthly transaction amount of at least $500 for every month of the past year?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year - 1, month: 1, day: 1 }) 
  AND date(t.transaction_date) < date({ year: date().year, month: 1, day: 1 })
WITH c, date(t.transaction_date) AS transaction_month, SUM(t.transaction_amount) AS monthly_total
WHERE monthly_total >= 500
WITH c, COUNT(DISTINCT transaction_month) AS months_count
WHERE months_count = 12
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customers_count

query: How many branches have at least one customer who holds every single type of loan product?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT b.id) AS branch_count
FROM branches b
JOIN customers c ON b.id = c.brc
JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id
GROUP BY b.id
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT l.ln_type_id) = (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM loan_types);
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH b, c, COLLECT(DISTINCT l.loan_type_id) AS loanTypes
WITH b, loanTypes, COUNT(DISTINCT loanTypes) AS loanCount
WHERE loanCount = 10
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT b) AS branchesWithAllLoanTypes

query: Count the number of customers with deposits and cards.
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customers.id) AS customer_count
FROM customers
JOIN cards ON customers.id = cards.cus_id
JOIN deposits ON customers.id = deposits.cus_id;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: Count the number of transactions per deposit type with ID 127.
sql_command:
SELECT dt.de_type, COUNT(t.id) as transaction_count
FROM transactions t
JOIN deposits d ON t.acc_id = d.id
JOIN deposit_types dt ON d.de_type_id = dt.id
WHERE dt.id = 127
GROUP BY dt.de_type
LIMIT 5;
cypher_command:
MATCH (d:Deposits)-[:HAS_DEPOSIT_TYPE]->(dt:DepositTypes)
MATCH (a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE dt.deposit_type_id = 127
RETURN COUNT(t) AS transaction_count

query: Count the number of loans per loan type with ID 127.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) AS loan_count, loan_types.ln_type FROM loans JOIN loan_types ON loans.ln_type_id = loan_types.id WHERE loan_types.id = 127 GROUP BY loan_types.ln_type;
cypher_command:
MATCH (lt:LoanTypes)<-[:HAS_LOAN_TYPE]-(l:Loans)
WHERE lt.loan_type_id = 127
RETURN lt.type AS LoanType, COUNT(l) AS LoanCount

query: Count the number of deposits per deposit type with ID 127.
sql_command:
SELECT dt.de_type, COUNT(d.id) as deposit_count 
FROM deposits d 
JOIN deposit_types dt ON d.de_type_id = dt.id 
WHERE d.de_type_id = 127 
GROUP BY dt.de_type 
LIMIT 5;
cypher_command:
MATCH (d:Deposits)-[:HAS_DEPOSIT_TYPE]->(dt:DepositTypes)
WHERE dt.deposit_type_id = 127
RETURN COUNT(d) AS numberOfDeposits

query: Count the number of accounts with more than 2000 in transactions.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT acc_id) FROM transactions WHERE tran_amt > 2000;
cypher_command:
MATCH (a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH a, COUNT(t) AS transaction_count
WHERE transaction_count > 2000
RETURN COUNT(a) AS account_count

query: Count the number of customers with accounts and loans.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) FROM customers c JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: Count the number of transactions with amount above 100 in the last 3 months.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM transactions WHERE tran_amt > 100 AND tran_dt >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '3 months';
cypher_command: MATCH (t:Transactions) WHERE t.transaction_amount > 100 AND t.transaction_date >= timestamp() - 3 * 30 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000 RETURN count(t) AS transaction_count

query: Count the number of transactions per account with ID 128.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM transactions WHERE acc_id = 128;
cypher_command:
MATCH (a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE a.account_id = 128
RETURN COUNT(t) AS transaction_count

query: Count the number of deposits per customer with ID 128.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM deposits WHERE cus_id = 128;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers {customer_id: 128})<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
RETURN count(d) AS number_of_deposits

query: Count the number of loans per customer with ID 128.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM loans WHERE cus_id = 128;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WHERE c.customer_id = 128
RETURN COUNT(l) AS loan_count

query: Count the number of cards per customer with ID 128.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cards WHERE cus_id = 128;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE c.customer_id = 128
RETURN count(card) AS number_of_cards

query: Count the number of accounts per branch with ID 128.
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches {branch_id: 128})<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
RETURN COUNT(a) AS account_count

query: Count the number of transactions with amount greater than average per branch.
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH b, AVG(t.transaction_amount) AS avg_amount
MATCH (b)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE t.transaction_amount > avg_amount
RETURN b.branch_id, COUNT(t) AS transaction_count

query: Count the number of deposits with balance above average per customer type.
sql_command:
SELECT dt.de_type, COUNT(*) as count_above_avg
FROM deposits d
JOIN deposit_types dt ON d.de_type_id = dt.id
WHERE d.bal > (SELECT AVG(bal) FROM deposits WHERE de_type_id = d.de_type_id)
GROUP BY dt.de_type
LIMIT 5;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits) 
WITH c, avg(d.balance) AS avg_balance, collect(d) AS deposits 
WHERE any(deposit IN deposits WHERE deposit.balance > avg_balance) 
RETURN c.customer_id, size(deposits) AS deposit_count

query: Count the number of loans with balance above average per loan type.
sql_command:
SELECT lt.ln_type, COUNT(*) as loan_count 
FROM loans l
JOIN loan_types lt ON l.ln_type_id = lt.id
WHERE -l.bal > (
    SELECT -AVG(bal) FROM loans WHERE ln_type_id = l.ln_type_id
)
GROUP BY lt.ln_type
LIMIT 5;
answer: [('Agricultural Loan', 10), ('Auto Loan', 11), ('Business Loan', 9), ('Credit Card Loan', 11), ('Education Loan', 10)]

query: Count the number of customers with more than three accounts.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (SELECT cus_id FROM accounts GROUP BY cus_id HAVING COUNT(id) > 3) subquery;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WITH c, COUNT(a) AS accountCount
WHERE accountCount > 3
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customerCount

query: Count the number of customers with more than three deposits.
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WITH c, COUNT(d) AS depositCount
WHERE depositCount > 3
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customerCount

query: Count the number of customers with more than three loans.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) FROM loans GROUP BY cus_id HAVING COUNT(id) > 3;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH c, COUNT(l) AS loanCount
WHERE loanCount > 3
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customerCount

query: Count the number of customers with more than three cards.
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) AS customer_count FROM cards GROUP BY cus_id HAVING COUNT(id) > 3;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WITH c, COUNT(card) AS cardCount
WHERE cardCount > 3
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customerCount

query: Count the number of transactions in the last 90 days per account.
sql_command:
SELECT acc_id, COUNT(*) as transaction_count 
FROM transactions 
WHERE tran_dt >= NOW() - INTERVAL '90 days' 
GROUP BY acc_id 
LIMIT 5;

query: Count the number of accounts with total deposits exceeding loans.

MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WITH c, COUNT(card) AS cardCount
WHERE cardCount > 3
RETURN COUNT(c) AS customerCount

query: How many customers have both loans and cards?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)

query: How many customers have both deposits and cards?

MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)

query: How many customers have both loans and accounts?
sql_command:

RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have both deposits and accounts?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS customer_count FROM customers c INNER JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id INNER JOIN deposits d ON c.id = d.cus_id;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)

query: How many customers have at least one blocked card and at least one active loan?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS customer_count
FROM customers c
JOIN cards ca ON c.id = ca.cus_id
JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id

cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(cards:Cards), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(loans:Loans)
WHERE cards.is_blocked = true
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: What is the number of customers who made more than 5 transactions in the last month?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year, month: date().month, day: 1 })
WITH c, COUNT(t) AS transactionCount
WHERE transactionCount > 5
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS numberOfCustomers

query: How many accounts have balances above the average account balance?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM accounts WHERE acc_bal > (SELECT AVG(acc_bal) FROM accounts);
cypher_command:
MATCH (a:Accounts)
WITH avg(a.account_balance) AS avg_balance
MATCH (b:Accounts)
WHERE b.account_balance > avg_balance
RETURN count(b) AS accounts_above_average_balance

query: How many loans have balances above the average loan balance?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM loans WHERE bal < (SELECT AVG(bal) FROM loans);
cypher_command:
MATCH (l:Loans)
WITH AVG(l.balance) AS avg_balance
MATCH (l:Loans)
WHERE l.balance > avg_balance
RETURN COUNT(l) AS loans_above_average

query: How many deposits have balances above the average deposit balance?
cypher_command:
MATCH (d:Deposits)
WITH AVG(d.balance) AS avg_balance
MATCH (d:Deposits)
WHERE d.balance > avg_balance
RETURN COUNT(d) AS count_above_average

query: How many cards have balances above the average card balance?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) AS num_of_cards_above_average FROM cards WHERE bal > (SELECT AVG(bal) FROM cards);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Cards)
WITH AVG(c.balance) AS avg_balance
MATCH (c:Cards)
WHERE c.balance > avg_balance
RETURN COUNT(c) AS count_above_average_balance

query: What is the number of customers who have both expired loans and expired deposits?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT loans.cus_id) AS customer_count 
FROM loans
JOIN deposits ON loans.cus_id = deposits.cus_id
WHERE loans.ln_en_dt < CURRENT_DATE AND deposits.de_en_dt < CURRENT_DATE;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans), (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WHERE date(l.end_date) < date() AND date(d.end_date) < date()
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS numberOfCustomers

query: How many customers have only deposits but no loans?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) 
FROM customers c
JOIN deposits d ON c.id = d.cus_id
LEFT JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id
WHERE l.id IS NULL;

query: How many customers have only loans but no deposits?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) as customer_count FROM customers c LEFT JOIN deposits d ON c.id = d.cus_id LEFT JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id WHERE d.id IS NULL AND l.id IS NOT NULL;

query: How many customers have both deposits and loans but no cards?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS customer_count
FROM customers c
JOIN deposits d ON c.id = d.cus_id
JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id
LEFT JOIN cards cr ON c.id = cr.cus_id
WHERE cr.id IS NULL;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans) 
WHERE NOT (c)-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]->(:Cards) 
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have deposits, loans, and cards all together?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS num_customers_with_all
FROM customers c
JOIN deposits d ON c.id = d.cus_id
JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id
JOIN cards cr ON c.id = cr.cus_id;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many branches have more than 20 customers?
sql_command: SELECT brc, COUNT(*) as customer_count FROM customers GROUP BY brc HAVING COUNT(*) > 20;
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)
WITH b, COUNT(c) AS customerCount
WHERE customerCount > 20
RETURN COUNT(b) AS branchCount

query: How many branches have total loan balances above 1 million?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT b.id) AS branch_count
FROM branches b
JOIN loans l ON l.cus_id IN (SELECT cus_id FROM loans GROUP BY cus_id HAVING SUM(bal) < -1000000)
WHERE b.id = l.cus_id;
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH b, SUM(l.balance) AS totalLoanBalance
WHERE totalLoanBalance > 1000000
RETURN COUNT(b) AS branchesAboveOneMillion

query: How many branches have average account balances above 50,000?
cypher_command:
MATCH (b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WITH b, AVG(a.account_balance) AS avg_balance
WHERE avg_balance > 50000
RETURN COUNT(b) AS branches_above_50000

query: How many customers made at least one transaction greater than 10,000?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customers.id) AS customer_count
FROM customers
JOIN accounts ON customers.id = accounts.cus_id
JOIN transactions ON accounts.id = transactions.acc_id
WHERE transactions.tran_amt > 10000;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE t.transaction_amount > 10000
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many accounts belong to customers who have blocked cards?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT accounts.id) AS num_accounts
FROM accounts
JOIN cards ON accounts.cus_id = cards.cus_id
WHERE cards.is_blocked = TRUE;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE card.is_blocked = true
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
RETURN count(a) AS account_count

query: How many accounts belong to customers who have unblocked cards?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT accounts.id) FROM accounts JOIN cards ON accounts.cus_id = cards.cus_id WHERE cards.is_blocked = False;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE card.is_blocked = false
RETURN count(a) AS account_count

query: How many customers have loans with interest rates above the average loan interest rate?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) FROM loans WHERE interest > (SELECT AVG(interest) FROM loans);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
WITH AVG(l.interest_rate) AS avg_interest_rate

query: How many customers have deposits with interest rates above the average deposit interest rate?

MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)

WHERE d.interest_rate > avg_interest_rate
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have both accounts and transactions exceeding the average transaction amount?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS num_customers
FROM customers c
JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id
JOIN transactions t ON a.id = t.acc_id
WHERE t.tran_amt > (SELECT AVG(tran_amt) FROM transactions);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
MATCH (a)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH c, AVG(t.transaction_amount) AS avgTransactionAmount
MATCH (a)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t2:Transactions)
WHERE t2.transaction_amount > avgTransactionAmount
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customerCount

query: How many customers have more than 2 different types of financial products (accounts, loans, deposits, cards)?
sql_command:
SELECT cus_id
FROM (
    SELECT cus_id,
           COUNT(DISTINCT product_type) AS product_count
    FROM (
        SELECT cus_id, 'account' AS product_type FROM accounts
        UNION ALL
        SELECT cus_id, 'loan' AS product_type FROM loans
        UNION ALL
        SELECT cus_id, 'deposit' AS product_type FROM deposits
        UNION ALL
        SELECT cus_id, 'card' AS product_type FROM cards
    ) AS products
    GROUP BY cus_id
) AS customer_product_counts
WHERE product_count > 2
LIMIT 5;

query: How many customers hold both loans of more than 50,000 and deposits of more than 50,000?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customers.id)
FROM customers 
JOIN deposits ON customers.id = deposits.cus_id 
JOIN loans ON customers.id = loans.cus_id 
WHERE deposits.bal > 50000 AND loans.bal < -50000;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WHERE l.balance > 50000 AND d.balance > 50000
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many branches have customers with blocked cards?

query: How many transactions occurred in branches where the average account balance is above 100,000?

query: How many customers took loans with interest rates higher than their deposit interest rates?

RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many customers have expired deposits but active loans?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT customers.id) 
FROM customers 
JOIN deposits ON customers.id = deposits.cus_id 
JOIN loans ON customers.id = loans.cus_id 
WHERE deposits.de_en_dt < CURRENT_DATE AND (loans.ln_en_dt IS NULL OR loans.ln_en_dt > CURRENT_DATE);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans
)
WHERE date(d.end_date) < date() AND date(l.end_date) >= date()
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS expired_deposits_with_active_loans

query: How many customers have expired loans but active deposits?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT d.cus_id) AS customer_count 
FROM deposits d 
JOIN loans l ON d.cus_id = l.cus_id 
WHERE l.ln_en_dt < CURRENT_DATE AND (d.de_en_dt IS NULL OR d.de_en_dt > CURRENT_DATE);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans), (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
WHERE date(l.end_date) < date() AND date(d.end_date) >= date()
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS expired_loans_active_deposits

query: How many accounts belong to customers who made transactions last year?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT accounts.id) 
FROM accounts 
INNER JOIN transactions ON accounts.id = transactions.acc_id 
WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM transactions.tran_dt) = 2022;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WHERE date(t.transaction_date) >= date({ year: date().year - 1, month: 1, day: 1 }) AND date(t.transaction_date) < date({ year: date().year, month: 1, day: 1 })
RETURN count(a) AS account_count

query: How many customers made no transactions in the last 6 months?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS inactive_customers
FROM customers c
LEFT JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id
LEFT JOIN transactions t ON a.id = t.acc_id AND t.tran_dt >= NOW() - INTERVAL '6 months'
WHERE t.id IS NULL;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers) 
OPTIONAL MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(t:Transactions) 
WITH c, collect(t) AS transactions 
WHERE size(transactions) = 0 OR ALL(transaction IN transactions WHERE date(transaction.transaction_date) < date().epochMillis - 15552000000) 
RETURN count(c) AS customers_with_no_transactions

query: How many customers have both blocked and unblocked cards?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) FROM cards WHERE is_blocked = true AND cus_id IN (SELECT DISTINCT cus_id FROM cards WHERE is_blocked = false);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE card.is_blocked = true
WITH c
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card2:Cards)
WHERE card2.is_blocked = false
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS customer_count

query: How many loans belong to customers who also made at least 10 transactions?
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH c, COUNT(t) AS transaction_count
WHERE transaction_count >= 10
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)
RETURN COUNT(l) AS loan_count

query: How many deposits belong to customers who also made at least 10 transactions?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM deposits WHERE cus_id IN (SELECT cus_id FROM transactions GROUP BY cus_id HAVING COUNT(*) >= 10);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH c, COUNT(t) AS transaction_count
WHERE transaction_count >= 10
MATCH (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
RETURN COUNT(d) AS deposit_count
